# Memory

**Location:** `~/.cursor/memory/` (local per machine, never in git)
**Full protocol:** See `context-memory` skill for read/write operations and entry schema.

## Namespace-to-Directory

| Namespace | Directory |
|---|---|
| `org.global` | `org/global/` |
| `org.security` | `org/security/` |
| `project.<name>` | `projects/<name>/` |
| `project.<name>.<domain>` | `projects/<name>/<domain>/` |
| `session.current` | `session/current/` |

## Capture Triggers

| Trigger | Category |
|---|---|
| Chose between alternatives | `decision` |
| Discovered hard limitation | `constraint` |
| Established pattern/standard | `principle` |
| Identified risk/concern | `risk` |
| Rejected approach with reasoning | `rejected` |
| Flagged work for later | `todo` |
| Produced architecture diagram | `diagram` |

## Store / Don't Store

**Store:** Stable decisions, constraints, principles, risks, TODOs spanning sessions, doc pointers.
**Don't store:** Raw chat logs, secrets/PII, large code dumps, ephemeral notes.

## Project KB Tags

Use `project-kb`, `doc-pointer`, `skill-lookup` tags. Include `source_path` for file pointers (repo-relative).

## Doc-Pointer Paths

Agent-generated docs live in `.cursor/docs/` (`plans/`, `decisions/`, `runbooks/`). Use repo-relative paths in `source_path`.
